<br>
Where: OBR Shadowbane Chat room<br>
URL: www.eqrogue.com/main/jIRC/chat3.html<br>
(Be sure to select 'OBR-SB' and provide your<br>
name in the NICK field.)<br>
<br>
Why: To organize strategies and to meet rogues <br>
from other organization. Analyze the <br>
Shadowbane Rogue. Ability to know what<br>
everyone else is thinking. Discuss information<br>
that is available today. A chance to find out if<br>
YOU are right for Shadowbane.<br>
<br>
When: March 25, 2001 Sunday at <br>
7pm Pacific, 9pm Central, 10pm Eastern<br>
<br>
Who: Anyone that desires to be master skilled at<br>
being a Rogue. True Rogues.<br>
<br>
Rules/Regulations:<br>
<br>
Chat will be moderated to make sure everyone gets their<br>
chance to discuss the topic that is important to them.<br>
<br>
There will be times when you are UNABLE to talk in chat,<br>
however, you are able to send private tells to anyone <br>
EXCEPT for the current speaker.<br>
<br>
Hold all questions till the speaker lets everyone know<br>
that he/she is ready to take questions. Send ALL <br>
questions to me/Kromel in a private tell. I will then<br>
send the question to the Speaker. I will discard all<br>
questions that have no relevance to the given topic<br>
at that time.<br>
<br>
Harsh language will NOT be tolerated and the result will<br>
be an immediate kick from the chat room. If the violation<br>
repeats, I will then issue a kick then a ban so the violator<br>
can not come back at all.<br>
<br>
The reason for this is that the time is late and people have<br>
to work Mondays. This will help make sure that all<br>
important topics are discussed quickly and keep the meeting<br>
going.<br>
<br>
*Friends<br>
<br>
If you have any friends that would like to know about<br>
Shadowbane and more importantly the Rogue, it would be<br>
a great opportunity to reel them in. We can use this chat<br>
to help them make a choice about Shadowbane.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
